-- Roethlisberger Runs, Throws for Touchdowns as Steelers Rout Panthers 27-3
-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 2010-12-24T05:01:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-24/roethlisberger-runs-for-td-passes-for-td-and-steelers-rout-panthers-27-3.html
Ben Roethlisberger  passed for a
touchdown and plunged 1 yard for another as the Pittsburgh
Steelers routed the Carolina Panthers 27-3 in a National
Football League game.  Shaun Suisham  added field goals of 26 yards and 29 yards
last night at Heinz Field in Pittsburgh. The Steelers, who also
got a 1-yard scoring run from  Rashard Mendenhall , led 20-0 at
halftime and 27-0 after three quarters.  Roethlisberger completed 22 of 32 passes for 320 yards for
the Steelers, who are atop the American Football Conference
North Division with an 11-4 record and had clinched a playoff
berth before the game.  John Kasay  prevented a shutout with a 27-yard field goal
for the Panthers (2-13) midway through the final quarter.  Jimmy Clausen  completed 10 of 23 passes for 72 yards and one
interception.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Nancy Kercheval  in Washington at 
